Class ResultsExporter

    Exporter<Query>, Closeable, Appendable, AutoCloseable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CSVResultsExporter

    public abstract class ResultsExporter
extends PrintWriterExporter<Query>
    An abstract class for exporting QueryImpl results.

    As with any PrintWriterExporter, the output can be sent to a PrintWriter, a PrintStream, or a String.

    The results are structured as a document that is sent to the specified destination, and has sections for

    • A header
    • QueryImpl data
    • QueryImpl answers
    • A footer

      • ResultsExporter

        public ResultsExporter(PrintStream printStream)
        Construct a new exporter whose output will go to the specified stream.

        The exporter will not close the stream when it is done, or even when its PrintWriterExporter.close() method is invoked. Thus this constructor can be safely used on System.out and similar streams that one usually does not want to close.
